Nursing Mothers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;Cabbi&quot; &lt;ca...@aol.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-08-18T02:12:00 </POSTDATE>
Good Christ, how much more horrible can the medical establishment make it
for women to give birth?
What do they do about caesareans?

http://www.cnn.com/2007/HEALTH/08/17/codeine.breast.feeding.ap/index....

First of all, codeine is a pretty shitty med for pain, but it works for some
folks. What did they recommend that a woman should do if she's one of the
poor souls who converts codeine to morphine too quickly? The doctor should
give her the smallest possible dose of codeine possible.

There must be better drugs that don't pass as quickly into the milk. If
there are none, there should be some allowances made for women who must
forego nursing in order to take pain meds. Soon the choice factor of having
a child will disappear. Then the health of the mother will fall away so that
the child will live, regardless of its disabilities.

I'm no big abortion fan, but I think it's going too far to take away all
choice from the mother who must dedicate her life to a child she's ill
equipped to love and nurture for the next 16 years or so.

Of course birth control would have been a better choice, but it failed on
some level. Whether it was ignored or simply did not block conception is not
important. One must deal with the results. If adoption isn't an option, (and
I wish it were far more often), what the hell good does it do to bring
another unwanted child into the world?

Just a thought,
Cabbi
