When my daughter was about 4 mos. old, my wife had an emergency apendectomy.
She was in the hospital for 3 days, and so I used formula during that time,
but when my wife got home, she was on Percodans for about 10 days, and what
I remember most about it was that it was super quiet the whole time she was
on them.  My daughter didn't appear altered in any way, but both she and my
wife slept like nothing I'd ever seen before.  We even called the doc and
double checked to make sure it was safe and was told as long as the med was
taken as directed, everything would be ok.  And it was.  Makes ya wonder how
articles like this would alter a docs precribing habits for nursing mothers
for short terms problems like described in this article.

